<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910131-0019</DOCNO><DOCID>910131-0019.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Asarco Inc.:   Fourth-Quarter Net Income   Fell 94%, Reflecting Charge</HL><DATE>01/31/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   AR</CO><IN>NON-FERROUS METALS (ONF)EARNINGS (ERN)</IN><LP>   Asarco Inc. said fourth-quarter net income fell 94%,reflecting a previously announced after-tax charge of $51.5million, or $1.24 a share, for environmental and royaltycosts.   The New York-based nonferrous metals company said net fellto $3.7 million, or 10 cents a share, from $59.1 million, or$1.42 a share, a year earlier. Sales rose 3.5% to $549.9million from $531 million.</LP><TEXT>   The one-time provision, which totaled $82.5 million beforetaxes, included $75.5 million in reserves to coverenvironmental costs associated with Asarco's current andpreviously closed facilities, as well as $7 million for theretroactive cost of increased royalties to Arizona.   Fourth-quarter earnings also were affected by lower lead,silver and zinc prices and costs associated with an eight-dayclosing of a smelter. But Asarco benefited from lower incometaxes, which were reduced a total of $19.3 million.   Richard de J. Osborne, chairman, said results were goodconsidering the economic uncertainties in the last half of1990. He said the environmental provision puts &quot;many&quot; of theuncertainties faced by Asarco behind it.   For the year, Asarco's net fell 36% to $149.1 million, or$3.60 a share, from $231.2 million, or $5.50 a share. Saleswere nearly flat at $2.21 billion.</TEXT></DOC>